ach\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1869}, {\"ngram\": \"his roster\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"a playoff game\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 1932}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few months before in the same state, a girls' field hockey playersuffered a painful injurywhen she was struck in the face by a ball.\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same state\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"a girls' field hockey\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 1994}, {\"ngram\": \"the face\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2057}, {\"ngram\": \"a ball\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2067}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports injuries are an unfortunate reality, especially in high-contact sports such as the ones mentioned above.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sports injuries\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2085}, {\"ngram\": \"an unfortunate reality\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2112}, {\"ngram\": \"high-contact sports\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2147}, {\"ngram\": \"the ones\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2164}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, a common thread in all of these instances is that these girls suffered injuries caused by reportedly male athletes.\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2306, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a common thread\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2206}, {\"ngram\": \"these instances\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"these girls\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2252}, {\"ngram\": \"injuries\", \"from\": 2262, \"to\": 2270}, {\"ngram\": \"reportedly male athletes\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2305}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's one thing to compete against someone on an equal playing field; it's completelydemoralizingto square up against someone with natural physical advantages that not only significantly decrease your chances of victory but also increase the risk of injury.\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2563, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one thing\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2348}, {\"ngram\": \"an equal playing field\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2431}, {\"ngram\": \"natural physical advantages\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"your chances\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2525}, {\"ngram\": \"the risk\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2552}, {\"ngram\": \"injury\", \"from\": 2556, \"to\": 2562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While international sports leagues like theInternational Rugby LeagueandWorld Aquaticshave recognized the harm in allowing men to compete against women, the Biden-Harris administration is actively working to continue this dangerous trajectory for women's sports.\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2722, \"end\": 2749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Biden-Harris administration\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"international sports leagues\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2599}, {\"ngram\": \"theInternational Rugby LeagueandWorld Aquaticshave\", \"from\": 2605, \"to\": 2655}, {\"ngram\": \"the harm\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2675}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2691}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2716}, {\"ngram\": \"this dangerous trajectory\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2807}, {\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 2826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The administration worked to tamper with federal law bychangingthe definition of \\\"sex\\\" in Title IX to include \\\"gender identity\\\" - a change that went into effect just asKatie LedeckyandSimone Bilesbecame two of the most decorated female athletes in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2919, \"end\": 2927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Title_IX\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.145863952843172e-24, \"text\": \"Title IX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Title_IX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Title_IX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The administration\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 2847}, {\"ngram\": \"federal law bychangingthe definition\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2906}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"sex\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2914}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"gender identity\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2955}, {\"ngram\": \"a change\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2967}, {\"ngram\": \"effect\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 2989}, {\"ngram\": \"just asKatie LedeckyandSimone Bilesbecame\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3031}, {\"ngram\": \"the most decorated female athletes\", \"from\": 3039, \"to\": 3073}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic history\", \"from\": 3077, \"to\": 3092}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If this rule change is allowed to stand, girls who look up to athletes like Ledecky and Biles could be relegated to bystanders in their own sports.\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3241, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this rule change\", \"from\": 3097, \"to\": 3113}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3140}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3164}, {\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 3170, \"to\": 3177}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3187}, {\"ngram\": \"bystanders\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3220}, {\"ngram\": \"their own sports\", \"from\": 3224, \"to\": 3240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A law change like this would elevate the situations highlighted in North Carolina and Massachusetts to a national scale.\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3309, \"end\": 3323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina_Tar_Heels\", \"score\": 0.9616965604682933, \"rank\": 0.03925373778843906, \"text\": \"North Carolina\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina_Tar_Heels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina_Tar_Heels\"}, {\"begin\": 3328, \"end\": 3341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\", \"score\": 0.6431573565653883, \"rank\": 0.5547055832890813, \"text\": \"Massachusetts\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A law change\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3254}, {\"ngram\": \"the situations\", \"from\": 3279, \"to\": 3293}, {\"ngram\": \"a national scale\", \"from\": 3345, \"to\": 3361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And up-and-coming female athletes would not be the only ones affected; all girls would see their private spaces - from locker rooms to hotel rooms on overnight trips - be open to male students.\", \"from\": 3363, \"to\": 3556, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"up-and-coming female athletes\", \"from\": 3367, \"to\": 3396}, {\"ngram\": \"the only ones\", \"from\": 3410, \"to\": 3423}, {\"ngram\": \"all girls\", \"from\": 3434, \"to\": 3443}, {\"ngram\": \"their private spaces\", \"from\": 3454, \"to\": 3474}, {\"ngram\": \"locker rooms\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3494}, {\"ngram\": \"hotel rooms\", \"from\": 3498, \"to\": 3509}, {\"ngram\": \"overnight trips\", \"from\": 3513, \"to\": 3528}, {\"ngram\": \"male students\", \"from\": 3542, \"to\": 3555}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alliance Defending Freedom, where I serve as legal counsel, is part of a large group of organizations and states trying to stop the effort to effectively erase needed distinctions between the sexes.\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3756, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alliance Defending Freedom\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3584}, {\"ngram\": \"legal counsel\", \"from\": 3603, \"to\": 3616}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3625}, {\"ngram\": \"a large group\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3642}, {\"ngram\": \"organizations\", \"from\": 3646, \"to\": 3659}, {\"ngram\": \"states\", \"from\": 3664, \"to\": 3670}, {\"ngram\": \"the effort\", \"from\": 3686, \"to\": 3696}, {\"ngram\": \"needed distinctions\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3737}, {\"ngram\": \"the sexes\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3755}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In five different lawsuits, we have achievedfiveinjunctions, or pauses, on the rule change, which takes effect while the cases proceed.\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3892, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"five different lawsuits\", \"from\": 3760, \"to\": 3783}, {\"ngram\": \"achievedfiveinjunctions\", \"from\": 3793, \"to\": 3816}, {\"ngram\": \"pauses\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3827}, {\"ngram\": \"the rule change\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 3847}, {\"ngram\": \"effect\", \"from\": 3861, \"to\": 3867}, {\"ngram\": \"the cases\", \"from\": 3874, \"to\": 3883}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are involved in defending state laws, likeIdaho'sandWest Virginia's, that protect women's athletics.\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 3996, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"state laws\", \"from\": 3922, \"to\": 3932}, {\"ngram\": \"women's athletics\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3995}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But still, as the emotional conversation around the Olympic boxing controversy showed, it's baffling that we have gone this far.\", \"from\": 3998, \"to\": 4126, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the emotional conversation\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4038}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic boxing controversy\", \"from\": 4046, \"to\": 4076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women deserve privacy, safety, and a fair chance to compete.\", \"from\": 4127, \"to\": 4187, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women\", \"from\": 4127, \"to\": 4132}, {\"ngram\": \"privacy\", \"from\": 4141, \"to\": 4148}, {\"ngram\": \"safety\", \"from\": 4150, \"to\": 4156}, {\"ngram\": \"a fair chance\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletic associations and government officials need to open their eyes to this reality and stand in favor of women against an ideology that threatens their unique place in humanity.\", \"from\": 4188, \"to\": 4369, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletic associations\", \"from\": 4188, \"to\": 4209}, {\"ngram\": \"government officials\", \"from\": 4214, \"to\": 4234}, {\"ngram\": \"their eyes\", \"from\": 4248, \"to\": 4258}, {\"ngram\": \"this reality\", \"from\": 4262, \"to\": 4274}, {\"ngram\": \"favor\", \"from\": 4288, \"to\": 4293}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4297, \"to\": 4302}, {\"ngram\": \"an ideology\", \"from\": 4311, \"to\": 4322}, {\"ngram\": \"their unique place\", \"from\": 4338, \"to\": 4356}, {\"ngram\": \"humanity\", \"from\": 4360, \"to\": 4368}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 The Federalist, A wholly independent division of FDRLST Media.\", \"from\": 4371, \"to\": 4440, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00a9\", \"from\": 4371, \"to\": 4372}, {\"ngram\": \"The Federalist\", \"from\": 4378, \"to\": 4392}, {\"ngram\": \"A wholly independent division\", \"from\": 4394, \"to\": 4423}, {\"ngram\": \"FDRLST Media\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4441, \"to\": 4461, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All rights\", \"from\": 4441, \"to\": 4451}]}]}"